#: ../new/drain.rst:9
msgid "Drain Weapon Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/drain.rst:11
msgid ""
"Unlike defensive structures or refineries, draining power plants always "
"affects the player's entire power, not just what is produced locally. "
":game:`Ares` adds some tags to make this customizable."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/drain.rst:21
msgid ":tagdef:`[TechnoType]Drain.Local=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/drain.rst:16
msgid ""
"Whether this unit drains only the local power from its target building, "
"or whether this building does not bring down the entire power grid of the"
" owning player when drained. If any of the draining unit or the building "
"drained have this set to :value:`yes`, only the local power is drained. "
"If both have this set to :value:`no`, then the victim's entire power is "
"drained. Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/drain.rst:31
msgid ":tagdef:`[TechnoType]Drain.Amount=integer`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/drain.rst:24
msgid ""
"The amount of power drained from a power plant of the victim player. "
"Requires :tag:`Drain.Local=yes` on either the draining unit or the "
"drained building. If positive, this is the maximum amount of power "
"drained. If negative, this is the minimum amount of power drained. "
"Defaults to :value:`0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/drain.rst:29
msgid ""
"The start value is the victim building's :tag:`Power`, then the draining "
"unit's :tag:`Drain.Amount` is applied, and finally the drained building's"
" :tag:`Drain.Amount`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/drain.rst:33
msgid ""
"For example: draining a Power Plant with :tag:`Power=500` and "
":tag:`Drain.Amount=0` using a Floating Disk."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/drain.rst:36
msgid ""
"With :tag:`Drain.Amount=-1000` on the disk, it will drain 1000, with "
":tag:`Drain.Amount=0` it will drain the 500 the building produces, and "
"with :tag:`Drain.Amount=200` on the disk it will drain 200."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/drain.rst:40
msgid ""
"If the building would have :value:`Drain.Amount=-600`, it would never "
"drain less than 600. If the building had :tag:`Drain.Amount=800`, it "
"would never drain more than 800."
msgstr ""

